properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 8 at 6:47PM CST until January 9 at 4:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...SNOW TONIGHT INTO THURSDAY ALONG THE NORTH SHORE...
...MIX OF SNOW AND FREEZING DRIZZLE IN NORTHERN WISCONSIN
THURSDAY...

.An area of low pressure and on-shore winds will cause snow to
develop along the North Shore this evening continuing into
Thursday. The highest accumulation will occur in the higher
terrain just inland from Lake Superior. Light snow and freezing
drizzle will be possible on Thursday over northwest Wisconsin with
some light icing possible.

* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of 3 to 6 inches.

* WHERE...Northern Cook and Lake, Southern Cook and Southern
Lake Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Grand
Portage Reservation.

* WHEN...Until 4 PM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM CST THURSDAY
